cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new algorithm for imitation learning using generative adversarial networks. It also involves optimization problems and evaluation of performance, which are common in machine learning research. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as imitation learning is a subfield of AI and the paper proposes a new approach to it. 

cs.RO (Robotics) is another likely sub-category as the paper evaluates the algorithms on two MuJoCo tasks, which involve simulating robotic movements. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possibility as the paper involves developing algorithms for controlling the behavior of an agent. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly involve visual data, but it could be relevant if the tasks involve image-based control.
